<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1052,1559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,1053,1079]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: ɗ 
<quantity box="[500,637,1053,1079]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="7.6" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="7.5">7.5–7.7mm</quantity>
. Body generally black; vertex with brown laterally near eyes; gena, lora and anteclypeus with brown patches; anteclypeus with pair of stout setae apically; scutellem with short tufts of black setae basally near lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[705,780,1133,1159]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[202,1377,226,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[181,1409,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cyrta tiantaishanensis sp. n. A, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; B, face; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182582/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs 
<number box="[764,780,1133,1159]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1052,1559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Male pygofer with subgenital plate extending nearly to apex of pygofer side (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1211,1173,1199]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[202,1377,226,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[181,1409,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cyrta tiantaishanensis sp. n. A, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; B, face; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182582/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1195,1211,1173,1199]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
G). Aedeagal shaft evenly tapered to acute apex in lateral view, slightly expanded subapically and narrowly rounded in ventral view, with dense small tubercles on distal half laterally; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1087,1253,1279]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[202,1377,226,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[181,1409,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cyrta tiantaishanensis sp. n. A, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; B, face; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182582/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs 
<number box="[1072,1087,1253,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
