<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1052,1559]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1413,1439]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar" authorityName="Melichar" box="[688,922,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cyrta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">
<emphasis box="[688,806,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. hirsuta</emphasis>
Melichar
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from it by: 
<number box="[1367,1380,1413,1439]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
) the black patch on vertex extending from posterior margin to anterior margin of vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1241,1453,1479]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[202,1377,226,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[181,1409,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cyrta tiantaishanensis sp. n. A, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; B, face; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182582/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1225,1241,1453,1479]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C); 
<number box="[1286,1301,1453,1479]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
) lora bicoloured (black and brown) (
<figureCitation box="[473,546,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[202,1377,226,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[181,1409,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cyrta tiantaishanensis sp. n. A, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; B, face; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, male genital capsule, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182582/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[531,546,1493,1519]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
A); 
<number box="[594,609,1493,1519]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagal shaft evenly tapered to acute apex in lateral view, slightly expanded subapically and narrowly rounded in ventral view, with dense small tubercles on distal half laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
